addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.5"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.5.xml"
number="5.2.5" /> and specialised to the case where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S=P^t]]></fr:tex>, this equation proves <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.3.1"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.3.1.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="5.2.3.1" />.
    In concrete terms, this implies that, to calculate <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R} a_*K]]></fr:tex>, we can proceed in two steps:

    
 <html:ol
xmlns:html="http://www.w3.org/1999/xhtml">
      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(a) &quot;">
        We take a resolution <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K\xrightarrow {\sim } K']]></fr:tex> such that the components <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[F]]></fr:tex> of <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K']]></fr:tex> satisfy <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R}^i {a_p}_*(F^p)=0]]></fr:tex> for <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[i>0]]></fr:tex>.
        The complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{a_\bullet }_*K'\in \mathrm {D}^+(S_\bullet )]]></fr:tex> (the derived category of the category of cosimplicial abelian sheaves on <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S]]></fr:tex>) can be identified with <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R}{a_\bullet }_*K]]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>


      
 <html:li
style="list-style-type: &quot;(b) &quot;">
        <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R} a_*K]]></fr:tex> is the simple complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {s}{a_\bullet }_*K']]></fr:tex> associated to the double complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[{a_\bullet }_*K']]></fr:tex>.
      </html:li>

    </html:ol></fr:p><fr:p>The spectral sequence <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.3.2"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.3.2.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="5.2.3.2" /> generalises to a spectral sequence

