xmlns:fr="http://www.jonmsterling.com/jms-005P.xml"><fr:frontmatter><fr:anchor>2261</fr:anchor><fr:addr
type="user">hodge-theory-iii-7.1.4</fr:addr><fr:route>hodge-theory-iii-7.1.4.xml</fr:route><fr:authors /><fr:number>7.1.4</fr:number><fr:parent>hodge-theory-iii-7.1</fr:parent></fr:frontmatter><fr:mainmatter><fr:p>We will need more precise results for the functors <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R} a_*]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[a\colon  X_\bullet \to  S]]></fr:tex> is an augmentation of a simplicial topological space.
    The case <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[S=P^t]]></fr:tex>, where <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R} a_*=\mathrm {R}\Gamma ]]></fr:tex> will suffice.</fr:p><fr:p>We reuse the notation of <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.1.12"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.1.12.xml"
number="5.1.12" />, and recall <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.6.1"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.6.1.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="5.2.6.1" />:
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       \mathrm {R} a_*       = \mathrm {s}\mathrm {R} {a_\bullet }_*.     ]]></fr:tex>
    For every complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[K\in \operatorname {Ob}\mathrm {C}^+(S_\bullet )]]></fr:tex>, the simple complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {s} K]]></fr:tex> is endowed with a natural filtration <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[L]]></fr:tex> (<fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.1.9.3"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.1.9.3.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="5.1.9.3" />).
    A quasi-isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u\colon  K'\xrightarrow {\sim } K'']]></fr:tex> induces a filtered quasi-isomorphism <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[u\colon (\mathrm {s} K',L)\xrightarrow {\sim }(\mathrm {s} K'',L)]]></fr:tex>.
    Then <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {s}]]></fr:tex> factors as
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       \mathrm {s}\colon  \mathrm {D}^+(S_\bullet )       \to  \mathrm {D}^+\mathrm {F}(S)     ]]></fr:tex>
    and <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[\mathrm {R} a_*]]></fr:tex> factors as
    <fr:tex
display="block"><![CDATA[       \mathrm {R} a_*\colon  \mathrm {D}^+(X_\bullet )       \to  \mathrm {D}^+\mathrm {F}(S).     ]]></fr:tex>
    The spectral sequence of the filtered complex <fr:tex
display="inline"><![CDATA[(\mathrm {R} a_* K,L)\in \mathrm {D}^+\mathrm {F}(S)]]></fr:tex> is exactly <fr:ref
addr="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.7.1"
href="hodge-theory-iii-5.2.7.1.xml"
taxon="Equation"
number="5.2.7.1" />.</fr:p></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:mainmatter><fr:backmatter /></fr:tree></fr:backmatter></fr:tree>